Create a new virtualenv.

Usage:
    vb new <virtualenv> [OPTIONS]

Options:
    -p python_executable  Executable to use. Defaults to $(which python3).
    -r requirements_file  Specify a requirements file of dependencies to install.

Create a new virtualenv with the specified name.

Setting -p /path/to/python or -p python3.6 will
specify a Python executable to use; otherwise
it will default to the value of $(which python3).

Setting -r allows you to specify a requirements
file of packages to install after creating the
environment.

The default python used by virtualb can be specified
by setting the $VIRTUALB_DEFAULT_PYTHON environment
variable.

